---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Operational Notes | Return Architecture"
  description="Notes on using a local environment for continuity, memory, and reflection responsibly."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <div class="eyebrow">Operational Notes</div>
      <h1>Using the setup well matters as much as installing it.</h1>
      <p>
        Architecture cannot solve everything. A local environment may create
        better conditions for sustained exchange, but pacing, review,
        boundaries, and self-observation still matter.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Pacing</h2>
      <p>
        Do not start by maximizing intensity, continuity, or access. A steadier
        rhythm gives you a better sense of what the setup is actually doing and
        how it is affecting you over time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Review</h2>
      <p>
        Revisit memory, logs, summaries, and retained material periodically.
        Reflection should not be automatic only at the system level; the user
        also needs deliberate review practices.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Boundaries</h2>
      <p>
        Decide what kinds of continuity you want, what should be remembered,
        what should expire, and what should remain outside the system
        altogether.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
